@*
    Help documentation view for PcApprovalRequestList component.
    Provides static help text explaining the component's purpose for displaying and filtering pending approval requests.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <h5><i class="fas fa-list-alt me-2"></i>Approval Request List Component</h5>
    
    <p>
        The <strong>Approval Request List</strong> component displays a filterable, paginated list of pending approval requests 
        within your workflow system. It allows users to view and manage approval tasks assigned to them or their teams.
    </p>

    <h6 class="mt-3">Purpose</h6>
    <p>
        This component is designed to show all approval requests that require action. Users can quickly identify 
        pending items, view request details, and navigate to take approval actions (approve, reject, or delegate).
    </p>

    <h6 class="mt-3">Configuration Options</h6>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Status Filter:</strong> Filter requests by their current status (pending, approved, rejected, escalated, expired).</li>
        <li><strong>Page Size:</strong> Configure the number of requests displayed per page (default: 10).</li>
        <li><strong>Show My Requests Only:</strong> When enabled, displays only requests where the current user is the designated approver.</li>
        <li><strong>Auto Refresh:</strong> When enabled, the list automatically refreshes to show the latest requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h6 class="mt-3">Displayed Information</h6>
    <p>For each approval request, the component displays:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Workflow name and source entity type</li>
        <li>Current status with visual badge indicators</li>
        <li>Requester information and submission date</li>
        <li>Current approval step</li>
        <li>Action links to view details and perform approval actions</li>
    </ul>

    <h6 class="mt-3">Usage</h6>
    <p>
        Add this component to any page where users need to manage their approval queue. 
        The component integrates with the Approval Workflow REST API to retrieve and display request data.
    </p>
</div>

